article.description: Erik McCree and Jacobi Boykins scored 18 points apiece to help Louisiana Tech cruise to an 87-56 victory over Alabama State on Wednesday night.
article.headline: McCree, Boykins lead Louisiana Tech over Alabama State 87-56
article.linkText: McCree, Boykins lead Louisiana Tech over Alabama State 87-56
article.story: RUSTON, La. -- Erik McCree and Jacobi Boykins scored 18 points apiece to help Louisiana Tech cruise to an 87-56 victory over Alabama State on Wednesday night. McCree and Boykins each shot 7 of 13 from the field. Omar Sherman had 13 points and Derric Jean added 10 for the Bulldogs (1-1), who shot 51 percent from the field. Mikel Tyson and Torloft Thomas had 12 points each for Alabama State (0-3). The Bulldogs never trailed and had a double-digit lead with five minutes left in the first half. The Hornets used a 13-5 spurt to pull to 43-31 at halftime, but they did not get closer. McCree scored 13 points and Boykins had eight in the first half. Louisiana Tech has won eight straight at home, and have not lost a home opener in the Thomas Assembly Center since 2006.
